{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":930,"text":"Even nature's most disgusting creatures"},{"time":3834,"text":"have important secrets,"},{"time":6401,"text":"but who would want a swarm of cockroaches"},{"time":7890,"text":"coming towards them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9484,"text":"Yet one of the greatest differences\nbetween natural and human technologies"},{"time":12496,"text":"relates to robustness."},{"time":14711,"text":"Robust systems are stable in complex"},{"time":17284,"text":"and new environments."},{"time":19005,"text":"Remarkably, cockroaches can self-stabilize"},{"time":20800,"text":"running over rough terrain."},{"time":22479,"text":"When we put a jet pack on them,"},{"time":23741,"text":"or give them a perturbation like an earthquake,"},{"time":25752,"text":"we discovered that their wonderfully tuned legs"},{"time":28643,"text":"allow them to self-stabilize"},{"time":30268,"text":"without using any of their brainpower."},{"time":33930,"text":"They can go over complex terrain like grass,"},{"time":37060,"text":"no problem, and not get destabilized."},{"time":39012,"text":"We discovered a new behavior where,"},{"time":40526,"text":"because of their shape,"},{"time":41690,"text":"they actually roll automatically to their side"},{"time":43768,"text":"to go through this artificial test bit of grass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47720,"text":"Robust systems can perform multiple tasks"},{"time":50157,"text":"with the same structure."},{"time":52295,"text":"Here's a new behavior we've discovered."},{"time":54162,"text":"The animals rapidly invert and disappear"},{"time":56008,"text":"in less than 150 milliseconds — you never see them —"},{"time":58509,"text":"using the same structures that\nthey use to run, their legs."},{"time":60872,"text":"They can run upside down"},{"time":62476,"text":"very rapidly on rods, branches and wires,"},{"time":65608,"text":"and if you perturb one of those branches,"},{"time":67087,"text":"they can do this."},{"time":68880,"text":"They can perform gymnastic maneuvers"},{"time":70410,"text":"like no robot we have yet."},{"time":72988,"text":"And they have nearly unlimited"},{"time":74719,"text":"maneuverability with that same structure"},{"time":77316,"text":"and unprecedented access to a variety"},{"time":81136,"text":"of different areas."},{"time":85406,"text":"They have wings for flying when they get warm,"},{"time":88029,"text":"but they use those same wings to flip over"},{"time":90643,"text":"if they get destabilized."},{"time":94600,"text":"Very effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95897,"text":"Robust systems are also fault tolerant and fail-safe."},{"time":99102,"text":"This is the foot of a cockroach."},{"time":100242,"text":"It has spines, gluey pads and claws,"},{"time":103531,"text":"but if you take off those feet,"},{"time":105122,"text":"they can still go over rough terrain,"},{"time":106830,"text":"like the bottom video that you see,"},{"time":108727,"text":"without hardly slowing down. Extraordinary."},{"time":112098,"text":"They can run up mesh without their feet."},{"time":115271,"text":"Here's an animal using a normal, alternating tripod:"},{"time":117554,"text":"three legs, three legs, three legs,"},{"time":119097,"text":"but in nature, the insects often have lost their legs."},{"time":122789,"text":"Here's one moving with two middle legs gone."},{"time":126799,"text":"It can even lose three legs, in a tripod,"},{"time":129715,"text":"and adopt a new gait, a hopping gait."},{"time":133642,"text":"And I point out that all of these videos"},{"time":135600,"text":"are slowed down 20 times,"},{"time":137304,"text":"so they're actually really fast, when you see this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139319,"text":"Robust systems are also damage resistant."},{"time":142830,"text":"Here's an animal climbing up a wall."},{"time":144643,"text":"It looks like a rapid, smooth, vertical climb,"},{"time":147139,"text":"but when you slow it down,"},{"time":148378,"text":"you see something very different."},{"time":150872,"text":"Here's what they do."},{"time":152520,"text":"They intentionally have a\nhead-on collision with the wall"},{"time":155527,"text":"so they don't slow down and can transition up it"},{"time":157641,"text":"in 75 milliseconds."},{"time":160039,"text":"And they can do this in part because they have"},{"time":161900,"text":"extraordinary exoskeletons."},{"time":163957,"text":"And they're really just made up of compliant joints"},{"time":167766,"text":"that are tubes and plates"},{"time":169499,"text":"connected to one another."},{"time":171042,"text":"Here's a dissection of an abdomen of a cockroach."},{"time":173989,"text":"You see these plates, and you\nsee the compliant membrane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177950,"text":"My engineering colleague at Berkeley"},{"time":180766,"text":"designed with his students"},{"time":181890,"text":"a novel manufacturing technique"},{"time":183371,"text":"where you essentially origami the exoskeleton,"},{"time":186982,"text":"you laser cut it, laminate it,"},{"time":188342,"text":"and you fold it up into a robot."},{"time":190737,"text":"And you can do that now in less than 15 minutes."},{"time":196554,"text":"These robots, called DASH,"},{"time":198493,"text":"for Dynamic Autonomous Sprawled Hexapod,"},{"time":201103,"text":"are highly compliant robots,"},{"time":204185,"text":"and they're remarkably robust as a result"},{"time":207887,"text":"of these features."},{"time":209690,"text":"They're certainly incredibly damage resistant."},{"time":215748,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":219101,"text":"They even have some of the\nbehaviors of the cockroaches."},{"time":221570,"text":"So they can use their smart, compliant body"},{"time":223843,"text":"to transition up a wall"},{"time":226360,"text":"in a very simple way."},{"time":229252,"text":"They even have some of the beginnings"},{"time":230880,"text":"of the rapid inversion behavior"},{"time":232199,"text":"where they disappear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235043,"text":"Now we want to know why they can go anywhere."},{"time":236520,"text":"We discovered that they can go through"},{"time":238089,"text":"three-millimeter gaps,"},{"time":239877,"text":"the height of two pennies, two stacked pennies,"},{"time":242238,"text":"and when they do this,"},{"time":243286,"text":"they can actually run through those confined spaces"},{"time":245861,"text":"at high speeds,"},{"time":247618,"text":"although you never see it."},{"time":250800,"text":"To understand it better,"},{"time":251862,"text":"we did a CT scan of the exoskeleton"},{"time":253940,"text":"and showed that they can compress their body"},{"time":255414,"text":"by over 40 percent."},{"time":258060,"text":"We put them in a materials testing machine"},{"time":259617,"text":"to look at the stress strain analysis"},{"time":261973,"text":"and showed that they can withstand forces"},{"time":264091,"text":"800 times their body weight,"},{"time":265995,"text":"and after this they can fly and run"},{"time":267885,"text":"absolutely normally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269875,"text":"So you never know where"},{"time":271598,"text":"curiosity-based research will lead,"},{"time":274672,"text":"and someday you may want a swarm"},{"time":276211,"text":"of cockroach-inspired robots"},{"time":278405,"text":"to come at you."},{"time":280819,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287940,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289497,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}